						               													<description>In Cloomba, which means &amp;ldquo;flowerbed&amp;rdquo; in some Slavic languages, the players become the Masters of flowers and butterflies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a colourful tile-placement family game in which the players aim to expand their areas in the beautiful Nature environment. The players make flowerbeds using double-hex tiles with flowers and place butterflies on them. The goal is to make meadows - the flower areas of the same colour. The challenge is that you can't place a butterfly on the meadow where there is another butterfly. These wonderful insects do not stand rivalry. Think of smart and artful ways to create separate meadows, and then unite them. &amp;#10;At the end of the game, each player scores points: flowers are multiplied by butterflies on each meadow.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cloomba contains a surprising amount of variety for a game with simple and intuitively clear rules.The game features an interesting market and superflower tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For more experienced players there are 21 option cards with extra points and abilities. All the option cards are unique: they do not replicate each other and allow a great range of strategy traded for butterflies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cloomba: Summer and Strategy in one box.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
